AB  - The proceedings contain 35 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Future Data and Security Engineering. The topics include: A Gloss Annotation Scheme for Enhanced Sign Language Translation; enhanceGuard: Lightweight and Robust Digital Watermarking with High Fidelity and Resistance to Image Degradations; Development of an Explainable AI System for Brain Tumor Diagnosis from MRI Scans; short -Term Stock Price Prediction Using an Ensemble Hidden Markov Model; cypherFuzzer: A Tool for Testing Access Control in Graph Databases; evaluating Sampling Strategies and Generative Models for Addressing Class Imbalance in Intrusion Detection Systems; CIDIX: Collaborative Intrusion Detection Through Human–AI Interaction and Explainable Visual Analytics; UABAC: A Flexible and Scalable ABAC Framework Unifying DAC, MAC, and RBAC; evaluating the Robustness of Graphs Against Link Prediction Attack Threats; on Online Self-Organizing Linear Search; Improving RFID Network Planning Efficiency with Genetic Algorithm - Hopfield Network Integrated Model; a Physics-Informed Neural Network for Modeling Chloride Diffusion in Reinforced Concrete Structure; dLTQueue: A Non-blocking Distributed-Memory Multi-producer Single-Consumer Queue; An Improvement of Distinguished-Bit Tracking Knowledge-Based Query Tree for RFID Tag Identification; task-Specific Ensemble Learning for Parkinson’s Disease Diagnosis Using Acoustic Features; Multimodal Stress Detection with LLM Using DAIC-WOZ; Optimizing MRI Brain Tumor Classification with CNNs and Stacking Ensemble Techniques; enhanced Detection and Classification of Pulmonary Diseases Using an Ensembled Convolutional Neural Network Architecture on Chest X-Ray Images; speaking the Same Traffic Language: A Florida – Tallinn Case Study in Cross-City Incident Prediction; Synthesizing GenAI Research in Developing Countries: A Review of Faculty Adoption and its Outcomes; v-Scribe: Structured Transcription of Vietnamese Speech for Digital Knowledge M