TI  - Discovering Deep-Tier Suppliers: LLM-Driven Manufacturing Site Inference for Enhanced Visibility
PY  - 2025
SP  - 13
EP  - 21
DO  - 10.1145/3764912.3770812
UR  - https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?eid=2-s2.0-105026345222&doi=10.1145%2F3764912.3770812&partnerID=40&md5=da9832fcc17928b1e00f5b656696f03d
AB  - The critical challenge of identifying deep-tier manufacturing sites in complex global supply chains hinders effective risk management. This paper proposes an LLM-driven Manufacturing Site Inference Technology to improve this visibility. Our novel approach employs a fine-tuned Large Language model to process diverse, unstructured, and sometimes contradictory data sources. It infers factory locations at the address level, which are then converted into latitude and longitude coordinates. The system uniquely leverages International Organization for Standardization (ISO) 9001 certifications, extracted via specialized prompt engineering, and is fine-tuned with domain-specific data including Harmonized System (HS) codes to enhance its accuracy. Validated against real-world procurement data, the technology achieves accuracy up to 86.7% in identifying manufacturing sites, facilitating a human-in-the-loop approach for verification. This provides tangible, site-specific visibility, enabling more effective risk management and enhancing supply chain resilience. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s)
