AB  - The proceedings contain 63 papers. The topics discussed include: the proactive gap: a scoping review of publicly available LLM-based browser extensions and their potential to mitigate information disorder; designing intent communication for agent-human collaboration; human, I need you: comparison of human-robot interaction modalities for search and rescue missions; advancing generative AI collaboration in design-to-code workflows: insights from two empirical studies; co-designing intelligent neighborhood technologies with young people to support communality in Nordic superblocks; Funnelectro: electrotactile funneling illusion and localization performance on the forearm; exploring socio-cultural expressions of interactive jewellery; teaching an old mouse new tricks: user-centered development of a gesture set for touch-enabled computer mice; and perceptual characteristics of EMS-induced finger flexion for bodily information displays.
