UR  - https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?eid=2-s2.0-105012244745&doi=10.1145%2F3736733.3736740&partnerID=40&md5=a3ef344bfa094293f05679ce93d580a6
AB  - Data discovery and table unionability in particular became key tasks in modern Data Science. However, the human perspective for these tasks is still under-explored. Thus, this research investigates the human behavior in determining table unionability within data discovery. We have designed an experimental survey and conducted a comprehensive analysis, in which we assess human decision-making for table unionability. We use the observations from the analysis to develop a machine learning framework to boost the (raw) performance of humans. Furthermore, we perform a preliminary study on how LLM performance is compared to humans indicating that it is typically better to consider a combination of both. We believe that this work lays the foundations for developing future Human-in-the-Loop systems for efficient data discovery. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).
