AB  - Large Language Models (LLMs) have revolutionized contemporary education, reshaping online learning and student engagement. This research paper explores the multifaceted impact of LLMs in education. Powered by Natural Language Processing (NLP), LLMs provide personalized, interactive, and adaptive learning experiences, catering to diverse student needs. The paper highlights the benefits of LLM integration in online education, including enhanced content delivery, automated assessment, and the creation of student-centric learning environments. Ethical concerns and challenges related to bias, data privacy, and algorithmic transparency are also investigated. The collaborative role of educators and LLMs is emphasized, underlining the importance of human-AI partnerships in education. The paper offers methods for measuring the impact of LLMs on education and explores future trends in LLM-powered education. The paper provides a global perspective on LLM adoption and utilization across different countries and regions. This research serves as a valuable resource for educators, policymakers, and stakeholders, driving the ongoing educational revolution facilitated by LLMs. © The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Switzerland AG 2025.
